Two Embu police bosses have said the death sentence should remain in force to reduce capital offences.Embu West subcounty police Boss Francis Sang and investigations chief Joshua Cheptoo spoke during a public hearing convened by the Presidential Power of Mercy Advisory Committee. They said convicted violent robbers murderers among others should be executed with a gun or hanging The two security bosses said the fact that convicted violent robbers, murderers, and other capital offenders are not practically hanged after conviction has increased such crimes in the country.They said during a public views hearing meeting at the Embu Cultural Hall on Friday if capital offences convicts were killed according to their sentences there would be minimal such crimes. They thus they said death sentences should be implemented to instill fear on the would be perpetrators of the crime and also to give confidence to witnesses to adduce evidence in capital offences cases.